1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
What if I told you some toxins are building up inside you right now?

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:11,600
This is bioaccumulation—a process where substances like pesticides and heavy metals accumulate in living organisms.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:18,000
These toxins can move up the food chain, impacting not just individual species, but entire ecosystems.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:25,600
In fish, for example, mercury can bioaccumulate at alarming rates, leading to serious health issues for predators, including humans.

5
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:31,200
Understanding bioaccumulation helps us push for policy changes to protect our health and environment.

6
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:34,000
Stay informed about toxins in your food.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Follow for more science insights!
